{"id":403580,"date":"2021-04-23T10:09:10","date_gmt":"2021-04-23T08:09:10","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/?p=403580"},"modified":"2022-01-11T17:18:41","modified_gmt":"2022-01-11T16:18:41","slug":"market-correlations-in-forex-trading","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/en\/market-correlations-in-forex-trading\/","title":{"rendered":"Market Correlations in Forex Trading"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><em>Understanding market correlations can provide you with an edge in the markets in terms of seeking new opportunities. Besides, knowing what assets are correlated can significantly reduce your exposure as you can diversify and deploy your resources elsewhere. In this article, we will cover everything you need to know about the market correlations.<\/em><\/p>\n<h2>Market Correlations in Forex Trading<\/h2>\n<p>Besides correlations in forex, there are also some interesting correlations in commodities and indices markets. Since FTMO is offering these instruments as well in form of CFDs, we will cover them in this article.<\/p>\n<p>Also, bear in mind that correlations very often break and they are more obvious on larger timeframe horizons.<\/p>\n<p>If you are focusing solely on day trading or short term trading, you will see that correlation between different assets are getting stronger and weaker.<\/p>\n<p>Correlation should be viewed as a factor of possible confluence, not be-all and end-all.<\/p>\n<h3>Equity indices and safe-haven assets<\/h3>\n<p>This is something we spoke about in our Risk-on vs Risk-off article. When equities and equity indices go down, the fear prevails in the markets.<\/p>\n<p>This means that traders and investors move their assets into the safe-havens such as Gold, Yen or Bonds.<\/p>\n<p><a class=\"lightbox-added aligncenter\" href=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-401606\" src=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2706px) 100vw, 2706px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12.png 2706w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12-300x176.png 300w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12-1030x604.png 1030w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12-768x450.png 768w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12-1536x900.png 1536w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12-2048x1200.png 2048w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12-1500x879.png 1500w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-13-at-9.46.12-705x413.png 705w\" alt=\"\" width=\"2706\" height=\"1586\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>In this case, we are talking about a negative correlation since one asset is going up and the second is going down, often with a high degree of mirroring.<\/p>\n<h3>Canadian Dollar and Crude Oil<\/h3>\n<p>Crude Oil is very important for the Canadian economy. Lower economic activity in Canada often equals lower demand for Crude Oil.<\/p>\n<p>Because of that, prices of Crude and Canadian Dolar are positively correlated.<\/p>\n<p>In the Forex trading world, it means that rising prices in Crude Oil equal to falling prices of USDCAD.<\/p>\n<p><a class=\"lightbox-added aligncenter\" href=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-401717\" src=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1510px) 100vw, 1510px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43.png 1510w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43-300x162.png 300w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43-1030x556.png 1030w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43-768x415.png 768w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43-1500x810.png 1500w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-10.56.43-705x381.png 705w\" alt=\"\" width=\"1510\" height=\"815\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Australian Dollar and Canadian Dollar<\/h3>\n<p>Both Australian and Canadian economies are heavily dependent on commodities.<\/p>\n<p>Australia is connected with precious metals (Iron Ore, Gold) and Canada with Crude Oil.<\/p>\n<p>Thanks to that, we can see a strong inverse correlation between AUDUSD and USDCAD.<\/p>\n<p><a class=\"lightbox-added aligncenter\" href=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-401722\" src=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1510px) 100vw, 1510px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25.png 1510w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25-1030x553.png 1030w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25-768x412.png 768w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25-1500x806.png 1500w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.21.25-705x379.png 705w\" alt=\"\" width=\"1510\" height=\"811\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Equity Indices and AUDUSD<\/h3>\n<p>Due to the Australian economy being dependent on export so much, there is a positive correlation between AUD and equity indices as they reflect the strength of the world\u2019s economy.<\/p>\n<p>If the Australian dollar is rising, we can see a positive correlation with the global economy.<\/p>\n<p>The most popular index to watch is the S&amp;P500.<\/p>\n<p><a class=\"lightbox-added aligncenter\" href=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-401726\" src=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1510px) 100vw, 1510px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22.png 1510w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22-1030x553.png 1030w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22-768x412.png 768w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22-1500x806.png 1500w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-11.47.22-705x379.png 705w\" alt=\"\" width=\"1510\" height=\"811\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Gold and USDJPY<\/h3>\n<p>There is a high negative correlation between Gold and USDJPY.<\/p>\n<p>If Gold goes up, USDJPY usually falls.<\/p>\n<p><a class=\"lightbox-added aligncenter\" href=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-401735\" src=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1510px) 100vw, 1510px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29.png 1510w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29-1030x553.png 1030w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29-768x412.png 768w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29-1500x806.png 1500w, https:\/\/ftmo.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Screenshot-2021-04-16-at-13.05.29-705x379.png 705w\" alt=\"\" width=\"1510\" height=\"811\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>This is due to the fact that both Gold and Japanese Yen are considered safe-haven assets, therefore when there is a fear in the markets, traders tend to move their capital into Gold and Japanese Yen.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Understanding market correlations can provide you with an edge in the markets in terms of seeking new opportunities. Besides, knowing what assets are correlated can significantly reduce your exposure as you can diversify and deploy your resources elsewhere. In this article, we will cover everything you need to know about the market correlations. Market Correlations [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":31,"featured_media":406303,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"inline_featured_image":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[670],"tags":[],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/403580"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/31"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ftmo.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=403580"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"h